1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,086
[man] <i>Where are you, buddy?</i>
<i>We have an operation.</i>

2
00:00:03,169 --> 00:00:04,462
<i>There's a shooting incident</i>
<i>at East Valley.</i>

3
00:00:04,546 --> 00:00:08,341
<i>A lot of children will die</i>
<i>if we don't accomplish this mission!</i>

4
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:10,176
[Marcus] Have you identified the shooter?

5
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:11,761
The shooter is also one of our students.

6
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:12,929
<i>He's a high school student, sir.</i>

7
00:00:13,012 --> 00:00:14,639
Erick is inside!

8
00:00:14,723 --> 00:00:15,724
Do you know his exact location?

9
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:17,350
[woman] <i>Oliver taught him</i>

10
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:19,811
<i>to always wear it in case of an emergency.</i>

11
00:00:19,894 --> 00:00:21,771
Don't worry. I'm going to save Erick.

12
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,523
[Marcus] <i>I wasn't able to save you,</i>
<i>Oliver.</i>

13
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:26,317
<i>But I promise,</i>
<i>I won't let you down this time.</i>

14
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:29,904
<i>I won't stop until I find</i>
<i>and save your son.</i>

15
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,906
- Daddy?
- Erick?

16
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:33,074
Uncle!

17
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:34,576
[Marcus] <i>Erick, I want you to go with him.</i>

18
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:36,327
He'll bring you to your mom, okay?

19
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:38,830
- Buddy, take care of him.
- Be careful.

20
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:42,417
[Felix] <i>Go to Damai Island.</i>

21
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:46,671
<i>Take all of the weapons</i>
<i>that Datu Rahman buried.</i>

22
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:48,465
[Jalil] <i>I'll teach you all of this</i>

23
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:51,718
<i>so you'll know how to defend yourselves.</i>

24
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:53,803
We must do this
to prevent another tragedy.

25
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:54,929
[man] Jalil!

26
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:56,473
Armed men are coming.

27
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:57,891
Move! Hide yourselves!

28
00:00:57,974 --> 00:01:00,060
- Roger!
- Go over there!

29
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:02,812
[Jalil] <i>Leave. Before anyone gets hurt.</i>

30
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:04,481
But there's eight of us here. And you?

31
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,149
[man] <i>They left you alone to fight.</i>

32
00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:07,817
We didn't leave him behind!

33
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:09,569
- [rapid gunfire]
- [grunting]

34
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:13,573
[Jalil] <i>Tell your men</i>

35
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:16,076
<i>to leave Damai Island alone.</i>

36
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:19,746
<i>The people here can protect themselves.</i>

37
00:01:19,829 --> 00:01:22,332
- [in Arabic] God is great!
- [in Arabic] God is great!

38
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:25,627
[Azuelo] <i>Save my son, Reyes.</i>

39
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:27,712
<i>Bring back Kyle, please!</i>

40
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:30,256
Gab! Stop, please!

41
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:32,675
I'll talk to Dad. I'll come with you!

42
00:01:33,259 --> 00:01:34,719
[both grunting]

43
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:38,848
- [gunshot]
- [people screaming]

44
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:43,144
[theme music playing]

45
00:01:56,574 --> 00:01:58,076
[alarm bell ringing]

46
00:01:58,159 --> 00:02:00,995
- [Gab sobbing]
- What did you do?!

47
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:03,123
[sobbing] What did you do?!

48
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:04,124
[sobs]

49
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:06,960
[people clamoring]

50
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:17,971
[grim music playing]

51
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:28,273
[whimpers]

52
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:34,779
[Kyle grunts, panting]

53
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:37,448
[suspenseful sting]

54
00:02:37,532 --> 00:02:41,077
[Kyle sobbing]

55
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,418
[sobbing] Get out of here!

56
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,546
Get out of here, or I'll shoot you!

57
00:02:51,629 --> 00:02:53,298
Leave now!

58
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:56,217
- Gab, please!
- Just leave! Get out of here!

59
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:59,971
[sobbing]

60
00:03:00,054 --> 00:03:01,973
[suspenseful sting]

61
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:05,018
[sobbing, screaming]

62
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:06,060
- Gab!
- [Gab panting]

63
00:03:13,109 --> 00:03:15,904
- Emil! Emil! [footsteps approaching]
- Sweetheart.

64
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:19,115
What happened? How's Kyle?

65
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:21,826
Don't worry. He'll be fine.

66
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:25,538
[tense music playing]

67
00:03:34,631 --> 00:03:35,715
[Kyle panting]

68
00:03:35,798 --> 00:03:37,342
- Sir!
- Kyle!

69
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:39,010
Are you okay? Huh?

70
00:03:39,093 --> 00:03:40,762
Are you hurt? Any injuries?

71
00:03:40,845 --> 00:03:43,389
Sir, I'm okay. But, Gabriel…

72
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:45,433
Gabriel?

73
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:48,561
Gabriel, he's one of my classmates.

74
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:50,521
He's the shooter, sir!

75
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:52,273
But, sir, please believe me.

76
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:54,776
He's not a bad person.

77
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:56,569
He only did this
because he was being bullied!

78
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:57,862
Please, sir!

79
00:03:57,946 --> 00:04:00,949
- Save him!
- Alright. I believe you.

80
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:02,075
Where did he go?

81
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:04,535
To the rooftop, sir. This way.

82
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:05,870
Please, sir, hurry!

83
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,789
Go ahead, Kyle. Get yourself to safety.

84
00:04:07,872 --> 00:04:08,873
Go on!

85
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:10,416
[suspenseful sting]

86
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:20,843
We are here live
at East Valley Montessori.

87
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,136
According to the initial report,

88
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:24,597
an armed suspect
broke into the school grounds,

89
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:28,977
which was later revealed
to be a student of said school.

90
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:32,563
Currently, we are seeing the suspect

91
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:36,317
at the rooftop of this building
holding a gun.

92
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:38,611
[police] Sir, sir! Ma'am!

93
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:40,738
Wait, Kyle's not here!

94
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:43,116
[sobbing] Why is Kyle not here?!

95
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:45,702
- [sobbing]
- Where's Kyle?

96
00:04:46,452 --> 00:04:52,458
[sobbing continues]

97
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:58,047
- [suspenseful sting]
- [sobbing continues]

98
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:05,138
- Kyle! Kyle!
- Dad? Ma!

99
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:06,431
[all sobbing]

100
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:15,773
[woman] I love you, son. I love you.

101
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:16,941
[exhales]

102
00:05:20,236 --> 00:05:22,447
[sobbing] I can't take it anymore.

103
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:25,325
I'm tired of everything.

104
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:34,959
Angeles, Domingo, Suarez,
pacify the parents.

105
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:36,294
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

106
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:40,715
- Zabdani and the rest…
- How can we do our job

107
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:42,258
if you're all over the place like this?

108
00:05:42,341 --> 00:05:44,385
Please move out of the way.

109
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:47,055
- Sir, our child--
- We're doing the best we can.

110
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:48,431
Let's please calm down.

111
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:50,641
Come on. Let's go.

112
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:53,436
Sir, I'll head upstairs.
I'm more needed there.

113
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,897
Everything's under control, sir.

114
00:05:56,564 --> 00:05:58,983
[Gab breathing heavily]

115
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:02,487
- [door slams open]
- [Gab gasps]

116
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:04,155
Stay away from me.

117
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:06,157
Gab…

118
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,325
Stay away from me!

119
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:11,370
You're a police officer, aren't you?

120
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:14,832
Get-- get away from me!

121
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:16,667
Gab…

122
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:20,713
[Gab panting heavily]

123
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:22,006
[gun thuds]

124
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:23,966
[sobbing]

125
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:25,426
Gabriel…

126
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,264
I'm Marcus.

127
00:06:34,977 --> 00:06:36,687
I won't hurt you.

128
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:40,066
I'm here to help you.

129
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,195
Let's talk. I'll listen to you.

130
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,118
It's all their fault!

131
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:52,870
Sir, it's their fault.

132
00:06:53,871 --> 00:06:56,749
Sir, I never did anything to them.

133
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,627
But they hurt me everyday.

134
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:05,049
They ridicule me everyday.
Mocking me, insulting me.

135
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:07,927
I'm tired of it.

136
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:11,722
[inhales sharply]

137
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:13,474
I don't want this anymore!

138
00:07:14,642 --> 00:07:16,853
I don't-- I don't want to go
to school anymore!

139
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:18,187
I don't want to live anymore!

140
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:19,480
Gab.

141
00:07:19,981 --> 00:07:21,816
Your life is precious.

142
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:23,526
You're right.
You didn't do anything wrong.

143
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:26,779
And you didn't deserve
to be treated like that.

144
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:28,948
But it's not too late, Gab.

145
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:31,951
You can still turn your life around.

146
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:36,330
You can still fix things
with the people who hurt you.

147
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,417
[breathes shakily]

148
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,835
Gabriel…

149
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:43,754
look at me.

150
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:48,050
I'll help you.

151
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,974
Hand that gun over to me.

152
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:00,855
No one needs to get hurt anymore.

153
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:05,067
Currently, we can see that at the rooftop
of the school building,

154
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:08,779
<i>Agent Marcus Reyes of Task Force Alpha,</i>

155
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:10,656
<i>talking to the suspect</i>

156
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,409
<i>and is trying to convince him</i>
<i>to get down safely.</i>

157
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:19,290
That's enough.

158
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:29,217
Just please hand it over.

159
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:44,065
- [gunshot]
- [Marcus grunting]

160
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:45,900
[people gasping]

161
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,779
[suspenseful sting]

162
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,576
[suspenseful sting]

163
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:58,162
Sir, I'm-- I'm sorry. I didn't mean to!

164
00:08:58,246 --> 00:09:00,122
- You didn't do anything wrong.
- I didn't mean to!

165
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:02,291
- Don't worry!
- Sir, I didn't mean to!

166
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:05,378
It's not your fault, Gab.

167
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:08,005
Sir, I-- I really didn't mean to.

168
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:10,299
- Ah!
- Gab!

169
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:12,510
- [Gab grunting]
- [Marcus gasps]

170
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:17,807
Marcus! Son!

171
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:18,849
Oh no!

172
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:21,310
Gab!

173
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:24,939
[Gab's mother] Gab, my son! Gab!

174
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:27,024
We're gonna save your son.

175
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:28,734
Sir, please move quickly!

176
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:29,735
[suspenseful sting]

177
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:33,281
[Gab screams]

178
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:36,909
STUDENT OF EAST VALLEY MONTESSORI
SHOOTS FELLOW STUDENT

179
00:09:38,035 --> 00:09:39,161
Gabriel.

180
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:41,163
Just hold on tight.

181
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:43,291
Please don't let go of me, sir!

182
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:46,794
Gabriel!

183
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:48,546
- Sir!
- [Marcus grunting]

184
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:52,758
Gabriel, don't let go! Just hold on to me!

185
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,552
[Gab] Sir, help!

186
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:57,138
I won't let go. [grunts]

187
00:09:57,221 --> 00:09:59,932
[crying] Sir, please don't let go!

188
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,350
[grunting]

189
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:02,727
[suspenseful sting]

190
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:05,771
[young Gabriel]
I can't hold on any longer!

191
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:08,899
- Marcus!
- [crying]

192
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:13,946
[tense music playing]

193
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,533
- [young Marcus screaming]
- Marcus!

194
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:18,951
Gabriel!

195
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:22,413
I won't let go, Gabriel.

196
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,002
No matter what happens. [inhales sharply]

197
00:10:28,085 --> 00:10:30,504
- Sir!
- You won't get hurt.

198
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:34,425
- [grunts]
- [suspenseful sting]

199
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:38,387
[suspenseful sting]

200
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:41,849
[groans]

201
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:48,689
[tense music continues]

202
00:10:54,195 --> 00:10:55,404
[grunts loudly]

203
00:10:55,488 --> 00:10:57,198
- [Gab groans]
- [grunts]

204
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:01,744
- [Gab groaning]
- [Marcus grunting]

205
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:03,871
Gab, hold on tight!

206
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:06,165
- [Gab groaning]
- [Marcus grunting]

207
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:12,088
[suspenseful sting]

208
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,591
- [both grunting]
- [Gab] Sir…

209
00:11:15,674 --> 00:11:17,885
[ominous music playing]

210
00:11:22,139 --> 00:11:27,478
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

211
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:54,505
- [Liam grunting]
- [Gab grunting]

212
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:55,423
[grunts]

213
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:59,009
- [Marcus grunting]
- [Gab grunting]

214
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:09,478
[all grunting, groaning]

215
00:12:12,481 --> 00:12:13,899
[sighs] Gabriel,

216
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:15,776
you're safe now.

217
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:16,735
[Marcus groans]

218
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:23,784
[breathing heavily]

219
00:12:24,368 --> 00:12:25,744
[in Arabic] <i>Praise be to God.</i>

220
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:30,791
<i>Good thing we managed to drive</i>
<i>those armed men away</i>

221
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:33,085
<i>without too many people getting hurt.</i>

222
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:34,920
<i>If things had gone differently,</i>

223
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:38,007
<i>it could've turned into another massacre.</i>

224
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:42,011
<i>Maybe right now,</i>
<i>we'd be burying our fellow villagers</i>

225
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:44,180
<i>and loved ones again.</i>

226
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:45,806
<i>[in Arabic] God is great.</i>

227
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:48,392
[in Arabic] <i>God is great.</i>

228
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:53,939
[breathing heavily]

229
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:57,943
["Maninindigan" continues playing]

230
00:13:05,784 --> 00:13:06,702
[Marcus grunts]

231
00:13:06,785 --> 00:13:08,329
Thank you, sir.

232
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:09,705
Thank you.

233
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:11,415
[sobbing]

234
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:12,791
Thank you, sir.

235
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:18,380
- [sobbing]
- [pats]

236
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:21,342
I know you're going through a lot.

237
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:25,221
Everything's going to be okay.

238
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:27,640
Stay strong.

239
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:30,518
Yes, sir.

240
00:13:32,102 --> 00:13:33,062
Come on.

241
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:35,814
I'll take him from here.

242
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:38,651
Come on. Come with me, kid.

243
00:13:38,734 --> 00:13:40,736
[grunts] I'll walk you outside.

244
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:43,697
[Felix grunts] Are you okay?

245
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:45,199
[Marcus grunts]

246
00:13:45,282 --> 00:13:47,868
Sir Marcus, let me check your wound first.

247
00:13:47,952 --> 00:13:50,496
[exhales sharply] I'm fine.

248
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,706
No, sir. I need to take a look.

249
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:55,084
We'll wrap it up temporarily, okay?

250
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:57,211
- [exhales deeply]
- Okay.

251
00:13:57,294 --> 00:14:00,923
Buddy, you scared me.

252
00:14:02,132 --> 00:14:03,050
- [Andre] Yeah, sir.
- [grunts]

253
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:05,261
I'm glad you're both okay.

254
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:06,595
Come on, you two.

255
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:09,139
Sir Marcus is built different! [chuckles]

256
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:11,517
That's what the former TFA guys
used to say.

257
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:13,811
They said he's like a superhero.

258
00:14:13,894 --> 00:14:15,187
[everyone laughs]

259
00:14:19,066 --> 00:14:25,114
["Maninindigan" continues playing]

260
00:14:25,197 --> 00:14:26,115
[music fades]

261
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:28,158
[pensive music playing]

262
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:29,952
[Gracia] Doc, they're here!

263
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:31,662
- He's here? Okay!
- Marcus!

264
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:32,955
- Let's go!
- Hey, guys!

265
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:35,165
- Marcus!
- Bring a gurney to be safe.

266
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:36,542
- Come on.
- Marcus!

267
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:37,835
- W-wait!
- Marcus, son!

268
00:14:37,918 --> 00:14:39,086
- Marcus!
- Ma.

269
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:41,422
- What happened, son?
- Ma…

270
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:42,798
Ma, I'm okay.

271
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:44,717
I'm okay. Just relax.

272
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,719
- Doc! Doc! Hurry!
- Doc?

273
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:48,262
Request an X-ray, please.

274
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:49,680
- Ma, relax.
- Hurry up!

275
00:14:49,763 --> 00:14:52,016
- Come on!
- Ma, I'm okay. Just relax.

276
00:14:52,099 --> 00:14:54,184
Doc, we'll take care of Marcus now. Relax.

277
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:56,270
- Come on, sir.
- Doc!

278
00:14:56,353 --> 00:14:57,187
Okay, have him sit down…

279
00:14:57,271 --> 00:14:58,981
I don't need this. I can walk on my own.

280
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:01,400
Sir, stop being stubborn. You need this.

281
00:15:03,193 --> 00:15:04,028
- [Marcus grunts]
- Don't worry, doc.

282
00:15:04,111 --> 00:15:07,072
We'll take him to the trauma unit
for X-rays and other procedures.

283
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:08,198
This way.

284
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:10,034
- Doc!
- Yes?

285
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:11,452
Don't forget the anti-tetanus shot, okay?

286
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:13,746
- Anti-tetanus, okay.
- And his blood type is AB.

287
00:15:13,829 --> 00:15:14,997
- AB?
- AB!

288
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:15,915
Copy that.

289
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:17,416
Okay, watch the corners.

290
00:15:19,126 --> 00:15:20,794
Okay, in, in.

291
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:22,922
Okay, bring the table.

292
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:24,214
Prepare the IV.

293
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:33,557
[grim music playing]

294
00:15:53,535 --> 00:15:54,912
[Ramli] Jalil.

295
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:05,255
What's wrong?

296
00:16:06,715 --> 00:16:07,841
Jalil…

297
00:16:08,926 --> 00:16:10,761
there's something
I need to confess to you.

298
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:15,224
Come with me. I'll show you.

299
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:22,564
[pensive music playing]

300
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:40,666
Does it still hurt, son?

301
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:43,085
Just tell me if you need
more painkillers, okay?

302
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:44,962
Ma, I'm fine.

303
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:46,797
Stop worrying about me, okay?

304
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,632
Oh, you always say that.

305
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:52,761
I almost had a heart attack
when I saw you on the news earlier.

306
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,722
- [Marcus chuckles softly]
- Oh, you really are something.

307
00:16:55,305 --> 00:16:56,557
I'm fine.

308
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:07,943
Why? What… What are you looking for?

309
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,945
- [Marcus] Where is it?
- [Teresa] Where's what?

310
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,947
What are you looking for?

311
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:16,076
- Wait…
- Oh, sir!

312
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:18,203
Is this what you're looking for?

313
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:24,793
Thank you.

314
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:30,174
So you kept it?

315
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:44,563
Gabriel?

316
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:47,858
We have lots of other toys.

317
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:50,903
Don't make your brother
work so hard fixing that.

318
00:17:50,986 --> 00:17:52,863
- But, Mama…
- Hmm?

319
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:54,531
It's my favorite.

320
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:57,743
When I grow up, I'm going to have a car.

321
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:01,580
Then I'll drive you and Marcus around.

322
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:02,915
[giggles softly]

323
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:05,542
Okay, son. Hmm?

324
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:08,921
There, I fixed it.

325
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:10,380
Yay!

326
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:12,132
My idol!

327
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:14,676
You're the best, Marcus!

328
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,261
I love you!

329
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:19,139
I love you too, Gabriel.

330
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:25,687
I feel like Gabriel's with me
whenever I hold this.

331
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:29,691
[sentimental music continues]

332
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:43,622
[music fades]

333
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:46,750
[morose music playing]

334
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:57,344
[fire crackling]

335
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:07,062
What's he doing here?

336
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:11,441
Isn't he one of the people
who attacked us?

337
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:14,778
And now you're protecting him?

338
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:19,283
Did you forget what he did

339
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:21,285
to our fellow villagers and families?

340
00:19:21,368 --> 00:19:22,578
Wait, wait.

341
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:26,206
Let's hear Ramli out first.

342
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:28,083
Let's not let our anger take over.

343
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:29,418
Just wait.

344
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:34,548
When the shooting started,
Tanaon got hit by a bullet.

345
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:38,594
Sir Harold saved him.

346
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:44,933
I'm asking all of you for forgiveness

347
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:47,227
for keeping this from you.

348
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:52,441
But I don't regret helping
and taking care of him.

349
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:55,819
Because while protecting my son,

350
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:59,198
he got shot and badly injured.

351
00:20:00,949 --> 00:20:03,493
Now, if sir Harold were truly
a bad person,

352
00:20:04,077 --> 00:20:06,455
he wouldn't have saved my son.

353
00:20:29,853 --> 00:20:31,730
This is exactly what I've been
telling all of you.

354
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,150
Even if they're our enemies,

355
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:38,695
we still need to show mercy.

356
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:41,698
Especially when
they can no longer fight back.

357
00:20:42,449 --> 00:20:45,160
Yes. Yes, we'll fight.

358
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,120
We won't back down.

359
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:51,833
But victory isn't measured
by how many people we kill.

360
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:56,713
It's also measured
by our ability to show mercy.

361
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:00,842
Like what we're doing for Harold here.

362
00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:23,031
Nurse.

363
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:26,326
What's the name of that nurse
wearing a hijab?

364
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:27,995
That one over there.

365
00:21:28,870 --> 00:21:30,831
[ominous music playing]

366
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:34,209
- Why?
- Nothing. It's just…

367
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:39,673
She's the one taking care
of my companion, sir Marcus.

368
00:21:39,756 --> 00:21:42,384
I just wanted to thank her.

369
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:45,554
Oh, her name is Jamilah.

370
00:21:46,930 --> 00:21:48,098
Jamilah.

371
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:50,767
Yes, she's very kind
and really good at her job.

372
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:54,271
And don't worry,
she'll take good care of your friend.

373
00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:55,856
Is that so?

374
00:21:55,939 --> 00:21:57,733
- Thank you.
- Sure.

375
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:04,781
[ominous music continues]

376
00:22:24,551 --> 00:22:25,761
- I'll kick you!
- Thief!

377
00:22:25,844 --> 00:22:28,555
- Let go!
- Hey!

378
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:32,476
[man] <i>Looks like our paths keep crossing.</i>

379
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:35,270
[Jamilah]
<i>You must really love your brother.</i>

380
00:22:35,353 --> 00:22:36,354
[Marcus] <i>Yeah.</i>

381
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:38,231
He just reminds me of my older brother.

382
00:22:38,315 --> 00:22:41,276
Why did the kids have to get involved?

383
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:42,861
Are we still doing the right thing?

384
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:44,196
Don't say that!

385
00:22:44,279 --> 00:22:45,363
- Listen to me!
- What's wrong with you?!

386
00:22:45,447 --> 00:22:46,406
[grunts]

387
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:47,574
[Jalil] <i>I'm leaving for now.</i>

388
00:22:47,657 --> 00:22:50,660
I'm going to bring Father back
and clear his name.

389
00:22:50,744 --> 00:22:53,538
<i>Once my mission is over,</i>
<i>I promise all of you</i>

390
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:55,332
<i>I'll come back here right away.</i>

391
00:22:55,415 --> 00:22:56,958
I need to finish this case.

392
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:59,294
<i>For kids like him.</i>

393
00:22:59,377 --> 00:23:01,129
For kids like Gabriel.

394
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,172
Gabriel!

395
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:06,885
[Marcus] <i>Who are you?</i>

396
00:23:06,968 --> 00:23:08,345
<i>Were you the one who blew up the ship?</i>

397
00:23:08,428 --> 00:23:11,765
<i>Are you the reason my brother died?</i>
